The '''Abyssal Sire''' is an [[abyssal demon]] [[Slayer boss]] that requires level 85 [[Slayer]] to kill. To access the boss, the player must have visited the [[Abyss]] at least once, either through the [[Mage of Zamorak]] or the [[Fairy rings|Fairy Ring network]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1189844286675783680|date=31 October 2019|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/98219|archivedate=20 July 2020|quote=Yeah, you need access to the Abyss, either via the Abyssal miniquest or via fairy rings.}} As with all other Slayer bosses, the Sire can only be fought when assigned abyssal demons (outside of [[Krystilia]]) or itself as a [[Slayer task]]. Although it resides in a multi-combat area, it is a solo-only boss.

According to [[The Overseer]], the Abyssal Sires are the engineers of the Abyss from a time before the God Wars. As their resources began to deplete and they had no means to escape, they constructed the [[Abyssal Nexus|Nexus]] and remained there in deep stasis.

It is known for dropping the [[unsired]], which can be placed in the [[Font of Consumption]] behind The Overseer for a chance of obtaining an [[abyssal whip]], [[abyssal dagger]], [[abyssal head]], [[jar of miasma]], a part of the [[abyssal bludgeon]] - the [[bludgeon axon|axon]], [[bludgeon claw|claw]], or [[bludgeon spine|spine]] - or, rarely, an [[abyssal orphan]].

The Sire was introduced in a [[Update:Dev Blog: Slayer Expansion v2|Slayer expansion developer blog]] on [[2 June]] [[2015]] and [[Poll:Old School Content Poll 34: XP droplets & Slayer|subsequently polled]] with 89.8% of the votes in favour of its addition.

